solo /ˈsəʊləʊ/

(solos) 

1. ADJ You use solo to indicate that someone does something alone rather than with other people. 单独的 

例： He had just completed his final solo album. 他刚刚完成他最后一张个人专辑。 

例： ...Daniel Amokachi's spectacular solo goal. …丹尼尔•阿莫卡奇精彩的个人进球得分。 

2. ADV Solo is also an adverb. 单独地 [ADV after v] 

例： Charles Lindbergh became the very first person to fly solo across the Atlantic. 查尔斯•林白成为第一个单独飞越大西洋的人。 

3. N-COUNT A solo is a piece of music or a dance performed by one person. 独奏曲; 独舞 

例： The original version featured a guitar solo. 原版以吉他独奏为特色。

